text: Conclusion may refer to: ==Media== *Conclusion (music), the ending of a composition *Conclusion (album), an album by Conflict *The Conclusion (album), an album by Bombshell Rocks *Baahubali 2: The Conclusion, 2017 Indian film ==Law== *Conclusion of law, a question which must be answered by applying relevant legal principles *Conclusion of fact, a question which must be answered by reference to facts and evidence ==Logic== *Consequent, the second half of a hypothetical proposition *Logical consequence (or entailment), the relationship between statements that holds true when one logically "follows from" one or more others *Result (or upshot), the final consequence of a sequence of actions or events *Affirmative conclusion from a negative premise, a logical fallacy ==Other uses== *Conclusion (book), the concluding section of a book *Conclusion of Utrecht, a synod of the Christian Reformed Church *Statistical conclusion validity, a statistical test *Sudler's Conclusion, a historic home in Puerto Rico, Somerset County, Maryland ==See also== * Closing (disambiguation) * End (disambiguation) * Final (disambiguation)
title: Conclusion
